cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with identifying pathogenic social media accounts on Twitter using graph-based metrics. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) is also likely as the paper deals with social media accounts and their impact on the spread of disinformation. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible category as the paper deals with identifying malicious accounts on social media. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes both supervised and semi-supervised approaches to identify pathogenic social media accounts. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible category as the paper uses graph-based metrics to distinguish PSMs from normal users.
